f=Cybersecurity/veil/custom/data-loss-prevention/SKILL.md · in=monitoring enforcement data egress controls detecting preventing unauthorized transfer sensitive data outside business's controlled environment. Combines **data-security-analysis** (Purview DLP event analysis, SIT/EDM monitoring, insider risk triage methodology) tool-agnostic custom DLP policy framework defines what protect, classify egress, who alert independent any specific DLP vendor. **Detection methodology from:** data-security-analysis (Microsoft Purview patterns, Advanced Hunting queries). **Policy framework:** custom (tool-agnostic). **Guardrail integration:** Sentinel Stack. · p=Data leaves business day through email, cloud uploads, USB devices, API calls, shadow IT. legitimate; breach progress. DLP distinguishes between two defining what sensitive data looks like (per classification tiers), it's allowed go, what constitutes violation detecting violations enabling response. · wu=Monitoring unauthorized egress sensitive data., "Are leaking data," "DLP alert review," "insider risk investigation.", Configuring tuning DLP policies., After breach involving data exfiltration reviewing DLP coverage. · h3:What Protect Classification Tier=**RESTRICTED**: Trade secrets, encryption keys, board communications, health records, payment card data. Monitor egress channels. Hard-block possible., **CONFIDENTIAL**: Customer PII, financial records, business plans, employee data, intellectual property. Monitor egress channels. Alert unusual volumes destinations., **INTERNAL**: Internal policies, operational data. Monitor bulk anomalous egress., **PUBLIC**: No DLP restrictions. · h3:Egress Channels to Monitor=**Email** sensitive data sent personal addresses, unusual recipients, large attachments **Cloud upload** sensitive data uploaded personal cloud storage, unapproved SaaS **Web/API** sensitive data API calls, web form submissions, paste sites **USB removable media** file copies external drives **Print** sensitive documents printed bulk **Clipboard screenshot** data copied unauthorized destinations **Shadow IT** data sent unapproved SaaS applications · h3:Alert Severity=\| Severity \| Criteria \| Action \| · h3:Alert Severity=\|---\|---\|---\| · h3:Alert Severity=\| **Critical** \| RESTRICTED data to unauthorized destination \| Immediate alert → operator + cortex IR \| · h3:Alert Severity=\| **High** \| CONFIDENTIAL data, bulk egress, known bad domain \| Alert → operator + security-monitoring \| · h3:Alert Severity=\| **Medium** \| CONFIDENTIAL data, single event, unusual \| Alert → operator review \| · h3:Alert Severity=\| **Low** \| INTERNAL data, policy violation, minimal volume \| Logged → periodic review \| · h3:Phase 1 — Monitor=**SIT (Sensitive Information Type) access audits** monitor who accesses what sensitive data types where. **EDM (Exact Data Match) monitoring** detect exact matches known sensitive data (e.g., customer lists, credit card numbers). **Sensitivity label access** monitor access labeled documents anomalous patterns. · h3:Phase 2 — Detect=**DLP policy match correlation** correlate DLP alerts across channels single user data set. **Insider risk triage** investigate users repeated DLP violations, unusual access patterns, data volume anomalies. · h3:Phase 3 — Investigate=**User drill-down** investigate specific user's DLP activity across channels. **File inventory** what files involved, their classification, their sensitivity labels. **Temporal patterns** activity time-bound (suggesting automated exfiltration) ongoing? · h3:Phase 4 — Respond=**Hard-block** RESTRICTED data unauthorized destinations, block action alert. 10. **Soft-flag** CONFIDENTIAL data, alert user log; escalate repeated. 11. **Escalate cortex IR** exfiltration confirmed suspected, cortex leads investigation. · of=`## DLP Investigation: [case/alert ID] \· Data involved: [classification tier \· data type \· SIT match \· label] \· Channel: [email / cloud / web / USB / print / clipboard] \· User: [identity \· risk score \· pattern] \· Severity: [critical/high/medium/low]` · pr=**Protect data, perimeters.** DLP follows data, network boundary., **Classification drives policy.** RESTRICTED data leak crisis; INTERNAL leak policy violation. Don't conflate them., **Hard-block RESTRICTED, soft-flag CONFIDENTIAL.** Blocking everything destroys usability; allowing everything destroys security., **Alert severity scales data sensitivity, volume.** One RESTRICTED record important 1000 INTERNAL records., **veil detects recommends; operator blocks/remediates.** security-inversion veil identifies violation recommends action; operator executes blocks user restrictions. · f=DLP tool deployed manual egress review, labeled "manual DLP." Flag risk warden., data-security-analysis skill installed use custom DLP policy framework alone, manual alert review., sensitivity labels applied use classification tiers directly; label gaps finding. · b:with Other Skills=**data-classification** (sibling): DLP policy driven classification tiers without classification, DLP policy enforce., **privacy-by-design** (sibling): data protection controls (encryption, access) complement DLP; DLP catches what controls miss., **breach-notification** (sibling): confirmed data exfiltration through DLP triggers breach-notification obligations., **cortex IR**: confirmed exfiltration escalates investigation containment., **cortex monitoring**: DLP alerts feed monitoring triage queue., **warden**: DLP coverage gaps unmonitored channels register risks.